single level inheritance. 
	class Parent 
	class Child


	Parent class Property :
		public default constructor -> print Parent()
		public greet() -> this function print good morning 

	Child class Property: 
		public default constructor -> print Child()
		public greet() -> this function print good afternoon 

	
	main:-
		1) create object of child class
			call greet function -> Parent() Child() g.a
		2) create object of parent class 
			call greet function -> Parent() g.m  
		3) create object of parent class using pointer.

	constructor in inheritance ->
		child object -> child constructor -> before child it will call parent constructor 

		greet() Parent 
		greet() Child 
			function overriding 
		
		Parent parent; //object -> dot 
		parent.greet();
		Child child; 

		Parent *p;
		p = &parent;
		p->greet();//object pointer type -> arrow 
		//good morning 		

		p = &child;//parent = child [ polymorphic object ] 
		p->greet();//good morning   [ virtual function ] [ pure virtual function ] 

		4 pm 

		

			
